Given this backtracking N-Queens solution:

```
N = 4
board = N x N matrix, all zeros
solutions = []

function isValid(board, row, col):
    // Check column
    for i = 0 to row - 1:
        if board[i][col] == 1:
            return false

    // Check diagonals
    for i = row - 1, j = col - 1; i >= 0 and j >= 0; i--, j--:
        if board[i][j] == 1:
            return false

    for i = row - 1, j = col + 1; i >= 0 and j < N; i--, j++:
        if board[i][j] == 1:
            return false

    return true

function solve(board, row):
    if row == N:
        solutions.add(copy(board))
        return

    for col = 0 to N - 1:
        if isValid(board, row, col):
            board[row][col] = 1
            solve(board, row + 1)
            board[row][col] = 0
```

